A memorial gathering for controversial filmmaker Theo van Gogh, known for his criticism of Islam, was held in Amsterdam's central Dam square.
Van Gogh, who made a film with politician Ayaan Hirsi Ali, was shot and stabbed to death while cycling in Amsterdam.
The Dutch Muslim community condemned the murder, drawing parallels to past assassinations.
The suspect, with ties to Islamic extremists, was arrested after a shootout with police.
Dutch society grappled with the loss of tolerance and unity in the face of radicalism.
Van Gogh's provocative work sparked debate on freedom of expression and societal divisions.
